  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification was performed across five flow-speed operating points. Validation experiments were performed at the sponsor laboratory and at an independent test facility; results are reported inline. Note: for several validation results the structured provenance link to the generating activity was not recorded at time of submission — the narrative references 'experiments performed under protocol VAD-EXP-2025' but the activity IRI was not captured for all result objects.",
